{
  "doc_id": "27301",
  "text": "Secondary traumatic stress may occur upon initial exposure, whereas vicarious traumatization is thought to involve changes in cognitive domains regarding self and others that develops from cumulative exposure to indirect trauma [CITATION_1] . This indirect or secondary exposure to traumatic material may take place in professional organizations, private practice settings, academic settings, and while the clinician or student/ clinician in training is at work, at school, or at home.",
  "correct_citation": {
